Feeling sleepy or tired, make the effort.

203
00:48:33,547 --> 00:48:34,929
Remember you can stand up.

204
00:48:37,351 --> 00:48:42,237
The breath is our anchor, it's our reference point.

205
00:48:43,777 --> 00:48:50,664
When we get confused or lost, we return to the breath and just remind ourselves that

206
00:48:51,487 --> 00:49:01,342
This is the simplest of exercises, just to observe, feel, experience whatever is within our awareness.

207
00:49:03,784 --> 00:49:10,635
Whatever we become aware of, that we observe, feel and experience.

208
00:49:12,518 --> 00:49:14,260
We don't do anything.

209
00:49:15,822 --> 00:49:18,306
We don't try and change anything.

210
00:49:22,588 --> 00:49:26,873
So hopefully now we feel more calm, more focused, we can open up.

211
00:49:28,034 --> 00:49:40,268
Whatever draws our attention within the field of awareness, inside and outside, that is the object to observe, feel, experience.

212
00:49:40,289 --> 00:49:41,309
It may be a sound.

213
00:49:42,791 --> 00:49:46,795
We're not concerned with the object making the sound, with the bird.

214
00:49:47,896 --> 00:49:50,519
We're interested in the process of hearing.

215
00:49:54,516 --> 00:49:58,300
maybe a sensation in the body, pleasant or unpleasant.

216
00:49:59,481 --> 00:50:05,168
We go to it if it calls our attention, feel it, experience it.

217
00:50:07,630 --> 00:50:13,317
It can be a feeling in the body caused by a mental state, depression, happiness.

218
00:50:14,918 --> 00:50:21,826
If it calls our attention, we go to it, we feel it, we observe it, we experience it fully.

219
00:50:22,666 --> 00:50:24,168
We don't do anything.

220
00:50:26,983 --> 00:50:35,233
If there's an image in the mind, as soon as we become aware of it, we just note imagining and bring ourselves back to the body.

221
00:50:36,735 --> 00:50:46,206
When we come out of a thought pattern, we just note what the attitude was that created it and just come back into the body.

222
00:50:48,309 --> 00:50:54,898
You may find that when you have an angry thought, for instance, as you come back into the body, you can feel it.

223
00:50:56,735 --> 00:50:58,117
as a physical state.

224
00:51:01,304 --> 00:51:05,193
And whenever we get lost, we just begin again.

225
00:51:05,213 --> 00:51:11,364
Always with the breath.

226
00:51:11,385 --> 00:51:15,974
Rising, falling, touching.

227
00:54:45,086 --> 00:54:48,891
Can you catch how you're reacting to what you're experiencing?

228
00:54:49,311 --> 00:55:13,574
How when something is pleasant there's a desire to maintain it to increase it How when something is unpleasant there's a desire to ignore it try to push it away turn away resist Noting that also

229
00:57:25,213 --> 00:57:34,262
and you become aware of how everything you're experiencing is arising and passing away nothing remains

230
01:00:42,382 --> 01:01:08,963
having accessed this observation post within ourselves a perch from which we can observe, feel, experience the body with its sensations and feelings the heart with its emotions and moods the mind with its images even thoughts if we're quick enough

231
01:01:11,592 --> 01:01:17,641
Can you see that when we're in this mode everything is happening of itself?

232
01:01:20,347 --> 01:01:22,951
Not because we determine or will it.

233
01:01:24,673 --> 01:01:27,257
It's all happening outside our control.

234
01:01:30,563 --> 01:01:31,304
It's not me.

235
01:02:54,260 --> 01:03:15,422
Perhaps you can sense a distance, a space between the observer, the feeler, the experiencer and what is being observed, being felt, being experienced.

236
01:03:15,443 --> 01:03:23,271
Although this isn't the fullest state of vipassana, here at least we can see clearly that sensation

237
01:03:23,554 --> 01:03:31,403
Feelings, moods, emotions, thoughts, images are there, not here.

238
01:03:33,206 --> 01:03:34,047
They're objects.

239
01:03:39,494 --> 01:03:40,534
Not the subject.

240
01:03:43,639 --> 01:03:44,500
Not me.

241
01:05:19,755 --> 01:05:27,507
Putting aside now all instruction, relaxing into the present moment, wide awake.

242
01:05:29,451 --> 01:05:40,086
Just observe, feel, experience whatever draws the attention within the field of awareness.

243
01:05:40,106 --> 01:05:44,092
And when we lose it, just begin again with the breath.

244
01:07:27,179 --> 01:07:31,164
When we come to the end of a sitting it's good just to reflect upon it a little.

245
01:07:31,184 --> 01:07:37,333
How diligent were we at bringing ourselves back to the present moment?

246
01:07:43,681 --> 01:07:47,646
How did we deal with the various physical mental states that arose?

247
01:07:49,369 --> 01:07:53,253
Were we skillful, unskillful, confused?

248
01:08:08,657 --> 01:08:30,987
Which of these three characteristics of existence, the impermanence of things, the role of wanting, not wanting, and this not me, not mine, which one of those was most obvious to us?

249
01:08:41,885 --> 01:09:09,494
penetrating any one of these three characteristics leads to liberation and then it's good to make a determination a real intention, intentioned for the next sitting or just as a general attitude

250
01:09:22,402 --> 01:09:37,007
And now we're going to do some walking meditation and being aware of that moment where we intend to rise just be aware of all the actions it takes to get us standing and then to put it on the circle.

251
01:09:38,069 --> 01:09:45,101
So if you just find a position on the circle all the way around the room intending to stand.

252
01:09:56,978 --> 01:10:26,344
walking meditation balances the sitting meditation and it's very good for developing the steadiness of attention focusing, concentration it's a much louder more obvious action than the breath and it's still neutral it's still neutral and all we're doing is just feeling observing, experiencing the sensations just around the feet so

253
01:10:26,542 --> 01:10:53,327
we begin by just feeling the feet on the floor and a noting word would be standing standing these words are just gently repeated and the purpose is to keep the intellect happy stop it wandering and when we feel established standing

254
01:10:54,386 --> 01:11:22,284
we make the intention intending to walk and there are four parts to the footstep the lifting as the foot peels off the floor moving as it moves forward falling as it moves to the ground or dropping and then placing as your weight moves into it and at that point there should be two feet on the floor

255
01:11:23,445 --> 01:11:49,284
and then the next step begins intending to walk lifting moving lowering placing lifting moving lowering placing

256
01:11:50,631 --> 01:11:53,841
If you haven't got the balance for this, just lifting, placing will do.

257
01:12:33,257 --> 01:13:00,631
and bringing ourselves to a standstill standing standing standing when that feels established intending to turn turning turning

258
01:13:11,664 --> 01:13:40,255
standing standing when that feels established intending to walk lifting moving lowering placing lifting

259
01:14:20,109 --> 01:14:49,306
and bringing ourselves to a standstill standing normally you would choose a place where you can do this for 10 maybe 15 steps backwards and forwards so now we're going to sit again and draw our practice to an end

260
01:14:49,743 --> 01:14:53,171
With goodwill meditation, loving kindness meditation.

261
01:14:54,333 --> 01:15:04,878
So make sure you take your time, being aware of all your actions, see if you can find a noting word to match them, stretching, pushing and so on.

262
01:15:07,064 --> 01:15:08,207
Intending to sit.

263
01:15:22,430 --> 01:15:28,297
The practice of loving-kindness transforms our understanding into an attitude.

264
01:15:35,708 --> 01:15:45,282
We have to be careful that the equanimity that we experience in the process of vipassana doesn't slip into indifference.

265
01:15:45,301 --> 01:15:50,850
And we do this by re-engaging, re-engaging with the world.

266
01:15:56,028 --> 01:16:03,755
Metta goodwill is not an emotion, it's an attitude.

267
01:16:03,774 --> 01:16:10,121
So you can practice this even when you don't feel so good, if you feel depressed.

268
01:16:10,140 --> 01:16:18,168
In time of course the heart resonates with the attitude but it's not necessary for it to do so to develop goodwill.

269
01:16:20,711 --> 01:16:24,954
That's why you can be kind to somebody even though you hate their guts.

270
01:16:30,942 --> 01:16:35,726
The four or five traditional blessings which you can use if you wish.

271
01:16:36,608 --> 01:16:37,488
May you be safe.

272
01:16:37,788 --> 01:16:42,554
Everybody wants to be safe from danger, both inside and outside.

273
01:16:44,596 --> 01:16:47,800
From within ourselves and from the world out there.

274
01:16:47,840 --> 01:16:51,963
Everybody wants to be healthy, well.

275
01:16:53,185 --> 01:16:56,970
Everybody wants to be free of distress, mental distress.

276
01:16:57,109 --> 01:16:58,131
They want to be happy.

277
01:16:59,882 --> 01:17:27,104
and to live a life which is contented more contentment in it happy with what we have and in harmony with the world even when the world is not so pleasant but to be in harmony with it, working with it safe, well, happy

278
01:17:28,266 --> 01:17:31,831
contented, in harmony with the world.

279
01:17:33,512 --> 01:17:47,210
And we start with our benefactors, bringing people to mind who've helped us, raises gratitude, and with gratitude it's easy to wish them well.

280
01:17:47,229 --> 01:17:54,139
And then we offer it to those who are near and dear to us, to friends, people at work and so on.

281
01:17:55,756 --> 01:18:00,301
To neutral people, people that we know, or we see rather, but we don't know.

282
01:18:00,320 --> 01:18:04,045
Neighbours, people we travel with, even people at work.

283
01:18:05,565 --> 01:18:08,850
We offer them the same quality of goodwill.

284
01:18:10,652 --> 01:18:12,354
Then we turn it towards ourselves.

285
01:18:15,917 --> 01:18:20,261
And in that heart of goodwill we can bring somebody in we find difficult.

286
01:18:22,942 --> 01:18:27,987
not that they are difficult, they just find themselves.

287
01:18:28,006 --> 01:18:52,171
Then we begin to radiate outwards, first of all to each other, to our neighbours, and here you can relocate to where you live, all the people in our country, all the peoples of Europe, all peoples on earth, and finally to all beings in all directions, so that this attitude of goodwill becomes universal.

288
01:18:53,569 --> 01:18:57,154
not determined by whether we like or dislike somebody.

289
01:18:59,877 --> 01:19:03,381
Bringing to mind a benefactor, somebody who's helped us in our lives.

290
01:19:09,287 --> 01:19:12,030
May you be safe, well and happy.

291
01:19:12,431 --> 01:19:16,235
May you live contented in harmony with the world.

292
01:19:27,319 --> 01:19:29,764
Bring to mind those who are near, dear to us.

293
01:19:35,193 --> 01:19:37,997
May you be safe, well and happy.

294
01:19:39,139 --> 01:19:42,645
Live contented, in harmony with the world.

295
01:19:55,061 --> 01:19:58,106
Bring to my friends, people at work, whomever we wish.

296
01:20:03,697 --> 01:20:06,641
May you be safe, well and happy.

297
01:20:07,103 --> 01:20:11,350
May you live contented, in harmony with the world.

298
01:20:28,340 --> 01:20:33,350
Bringing to mind a neutral person or persons, people we see but don't know.

299
01:20:35,996 --> 01:20:42,529
Offering them the same quality of goodwill.

300
01:20:42,548 --> 01:20:44,793
May you be safe, well and happy.

301
01:20:45,314 --> 01:20:49,403
May you live contented, in harmony with the world.

302
01:21:05,396 --> 01:21:08,942
Turning now that stream of goodwill towards ourselves.

303
01:21:10,264 --> 01:21:13,127
May I be safe, well and happy.

304
01:21:13,448 --> 01:21:17,373
May I live contented, in harmony with the world.

305
01:21:30,872 --> 01:21:34,137
And into the heart of goodwill, someone we find difficult.

306
01:21:40,042 --> 01:21:42,564
May you be safe, well and happy.

307
01:21:43,185 --> 01:21:47,167
May you live contented, in harmony with the world.

308
01:22:02,582 --> 01:22:08,648
Beginning now to radiate outwards, first of all to each other, our spiritual companions.

309
01:22:11,024 --> 01:22:13,287
May we be safe, well and happy.

310
01:22:14,009 --> 01:22:17,795
May we live contented in harmony with the world.

311
01:22:33,840 --> 01:22:38,027
To our neighbours, remember we can relocate to where we live.

312
01:22:57,412 --> 01:23:22,694
all the people in our country all the peoples of Europe

313
01:23:43,954 --> 01:23:55,820
All people on earth, and as you scan the globe, hover a little while over those places where there's war, natural disaster, poverty.

314
01:24:18,632 --> 01:24:22,533
And finally, to all beings in all directions.

315
01:24:49,818 --> 01:25:14,677
and we end with a little chant SABHE SATA SUKHITA HANTU which means may all beings be happy and then SADU SADU SADU which means well done three times SABHE SATA SUKHITA HANTU

316
01:25:15,180 --> 01:25:45,188
Sabe satta sukita hantu Sabe satta sukita hantu Sadhu sadhu sadhu

317
01:25:45,421 --> 01:26:15,175
take this mindfulness with you now to you know, until you fall asleep, see, so just take your time make every action deliberate, see don't do an action which you didn't know you were doing so these noting, this little noting can be very helpful to do that, see you have to slow down, slow down all these actions that we do every day, see, they become numbed, see

318
01:26:15,813 --> 01:26:19,737
When was the last time you tasted your toothpaste?

319
01:26:19,756 --> 01:26:22,439
And if you really tasted your toothpaste, would you buy that one again?

320
01:26:26,384 --> 01:26:37,555
And finally, when you get to bed, you're lying down, especially those of you who have difficulty sleeping, you do this practice of metta, you see.

321
01:26:38,536 --> 01:26:44,942
Make it very simple, just somebody whom you have no problems with, if there is anybody,

322
01:26:46,171 --> 01:26:48,233
If not, just somebody you don't have problems with.

323
01:26:49,835 --> 01:26:56,322
And then to yourself, and then to all beings, and choose a very simple phrase, like, may you be happy.

324
01:26:57,944 --> 01:27:00,346
And just keep repeating that, just very gently, you see.

325
01:27:01,148 --> 01:27:07,975
And it creates a certain level of concentration, and that becomes the substrate of your sleep, you see.

326
01:27:07,994 --> 01:27:09,317
That makes you sleep more peacefully.

327
01:27:10,797 --> 01:27:14,101
Or just the breath, just the calmness of the breath, you see.

328
01:27:16,427 --> 01:27:28,422
if you find yourself being very, very restless, tossing from one side to the other, try just lying very still and refusing, under all circumstances, to move.

329
01:27:31,367 --> 01:27:34,712
You may be surprised to find that you suddenly wake up tomorrow morning.

330
01:27:37,314 --> 01:27:43,582
And of course, you mustn't fall asleep without making a severe determination to wake with the bell.

331
01:27:46,177 --> 01:27:47,345
We'll be right back.
